     712       18227 :       SUBROUTINE DESUBI
     713       18227 :      +   (N,M,WD,LDWD,LD2WD,ALPHA,TT,LDTT,I,E)
     714             : C***BEGIN PROLOGUE  DESUBI
     715             : C***REFER TO  DODR,DODRC
     716             : C***ROUTINES CALLED  DZERO
     717             : C***DATE WRITTEN   860529   (YYMMDD)
     718             : C***REVISION DATE  920304   (YYMMDD)
     719             : C***PURPOSE  COMPUTE E = WD + ALPHA*TT**2
     720             : C***END PROLOGUE  DESUBI
     721             : 
     722             : C...SCALAR ARGUMENTS
     723             :       DOUBLE PRECISION
     724             :      +   ALPHA

     726             :      +   LDTT,LDWD,LD2WD,M,N
     727             : 
     728             : C...ARRAY ARGUMENTS
     729             :       DOUBLE PRECISION

     731             : 
     732             : C...LOCAL SCALARS
     733             :       DOUBLE PRECISION
     734             :      +   ZERO
     735             :       INTEGER
     736             :      +   I,J,J1,J2
     737             : 
     738             : C...EXTERNAL SUBROUTINES
     739             :       EXTERNAL
     740             :      +   DZERO
     741             : 
     742             : C...DATA STATEMENTS
     743             :       DATA
     744             :      +   ZERO
     745             :      +   /0.0D0/
     746             : 
     747             : C...VARIABLE DEFINITIONS (ALPHABETICALLY)
     748             : C   ALPHA:  THE LEVENBERG-MARQUARDT PARAMETER.
     749             : C   E:      THE VALUE OF THE ARRAY E = WD + ALPHA*TT**2
     750             : C   I:      AN INDEXING VARIABLE.
     751             : C   J:      AN INDEXING VARIABLE.
     752             : C   J1:     AN INDEXING VARIABLE.
     753             : C   J2:     AN INDEXING VARIABLE.
     754             : C   LDWD:   THE LEADING DIMENSION OF ARRAY WD.
     755             : C   LD2WD:  THE SECOND DIMENSION OF ARRAY WD.
     756             : C   M:      THE NUMBER OF COLUMNS OF DATA IN THE INDEPENDENT VARIABLE.
     757             : C   N:      THE NUMBER OF OBSERVATIONS.
     758             : C   NP:     THE NUMBER OF RESPONSES PER OBSERVATION.
     759             : C   TT:     THE SCALING VALUES USED FOR DELTA.
     760             : C   WD:     THE SQUARED DELTA WEIGHTS, D**2.
     761             : C   ZERO:   THE VALUE 0.0D0.
     762             : 
     763             : 
     764             : C***FIRST EXECUTABLE STATEMENT  DESUBI
     765             : 
     766             : 
     767             : C   N.B. THE LOCATIONS OF WD AND TT ACCESSED DEPEND ON THE VALUE
     768             : C        OF THE FIRST ELEMENT OF EACH ARRAY AND THE LEADING DIMENSIONS
     769             : C        OF THE MULTIPLY SUBSCRIPTED ARRAYS.
     770             : 
     771       18227 :       IF (N.EQ.0 .OR. M.EQ.0) RETURN
     772             :

    7013             : C   ANAJAC:  THE VARIABLE DESIGNATING WHETHER THE JACOBIANS ARE COMPUTED
    7014             : C            BY FINITE DIFFERENCES (ANAJAC=FALSE) OR NOT (ANAJAC=TRUE).
    7015             : C   BETA:    THE FUNCTION PARAMETERS.
    7016             : C   D1:      THE FIRST DIGIT OF INFO.
    7017             : C   D2:      THE SECOND DIGIT OF INFO.
    7018             : C   D3:      THE THIRD DIGIT OF INFO.
    7019             : C   D4:      THE FOURTH DIGIT OF INFO.
    7020             : C   D5:      THE FIFTH DIGIT OF INFO.
    7021             : C   DELTA:   THE ESTIMATED ERRORS IN THE EXPLANATORY VARIABLES.
    7022             : C   DIDVCV:  THE VARIABLE DESIGNATING WHETHER THE COVARIANCE MATRIX WAS
    7023             : C            COMPUTED (DIDVCV=TRUE) OR NOT (DIDVCV=FALSE).
    7024             : C   DOVCV:   THE VARIABLE DESIGNATING WHETHER THE COVARIANCE MATRIX WAS
    7025             : C            TO BE COMPUTED (DOVCV=TRUE) OR NOT (DOVCV=FALSE).
    7026             : C   F:       THE ESTIMATED VALUES OF EPSILON.
    7027             : C   FMT1:    A CHARACTER*90 VARIABLE USED FOR FORMATS.
    7028             : C   I:       AN INDEXING VARIABLE.
    7029             : C   IDF:     THE DEGREES OF FREEDOM OF THE FIT, EQUAL TO THE NUMBER OF
    7030             : C            OBSERVATIONS WITH NONZERO WEIGHTED DERIVATIVES MINUS THE
    7031             : C            NUMBER OF PARAMETERS BEING ESTIMATED.
    7032             : C   IFIXB2:  THE VALUES DESIGNATING WHETHER THE ELEMENTS OF BETA WERE 
    7033             : C            ESTIMATED, FIXED, OR DROPPED BECAUSE THEY CAUSED RANK 
    7034             : C            DEFICIENCY, CORRESPONDING TO VALUES OF IFIXB2 EQUALING 1,
    7035             : C            0, AND -1, RESPECTIVELY.  IF IFIXB2 IS -2, THEN NO ATTEMPT
    7036             : C            WAS MADE TO ESTIMATE THE PARAMETERS BECAUSE MAXIT = 0.
    7037             : C   IMPLCT:  THE VARIABLE DESIGNATING WHETHER THE SOLUTION IS BY 
    7038             : C            IMPLICIT ODR (IMPLCT=TRUE) OR EXPLICIT ODR (IMPLCT=FALSE).
    7039             : C   INFO:    THE VARIABLE DESIGNATING WHY THE COMPUTATIONS WERE STOPPED.
    7040             : C   IPR:     THE VARIABLE INDICATING WHAT IS TO BE PRINTED.
    7041             : C   IRANK:   THE RANK DEFICIENCY OF THE JACOBIAN WRT BETA.
    7042             : C   ISODR:   THE VARIABLE DESIGNATING WHETHER THE SOLUTION IS BY ODR 
    7043             : C            (ISODR=TRUE) OR BY OLS (ISODR=FALSE).
    7044             : C   ISTOP:   THE VARIABLE DESIGNATING WHETHER THERE ARE PROBLEMS
    7045             : C            COMPUTING THE FUNCTION AT THE CURRENT BETA AND DELTA.
    7046             : C   J:       AN INDEXING VARIABLE.
    7047             : C   K:       AN INDEXING VARIABLE.
    7048             : C   L:       AN INDEXING VARIABLE.
    7049             : C   LUNRPT:  THE LOGICAL UNIT NUMBER USED FOR COMPUTATION REPORTS.
    7050             : C   M:       THE NUMBER OF COLUMNS OF DATA IN THE EXPLANATORY VARIABLE.
    7051             : C   N:       THE NUMBER OF OBSERVATIONS.
    7052             : C   NFEV:    THE NUMBER OF FUNCTION EVALUATIONS.
    7053             : C   NITER:   THE NUMBER OF ITERATIONS.
    7054             : C   NJEV:    THE NUMBER OF JACOBIAN EVALUATIONS.
    7055             : C   NP:      THE NUMBER OF FUNCTION PARAMETERS.
    7056             : C   NPLM1:   THE NUMBER OF ITEMS TO BE PRINTED PER LINE, MINUS ONE.
    7057             : C   NPP:     THE NUMBER OF FUNCTION PARAMETERS BEING ESTIMATED.
    7058             : C   NQ:      THE NUMBER OF RESPONSES PER OBSERVATION.
    7059             : C   PNLTY:   THE PENALTY PARAMETER FOR AN IMPLICIT MODEL.
    7060             : C   RCOND:   THE APPROXIMATE RECIPROCAL CONDITION OF TFJACB.
    7061             : C   REDOJ:   THE VARIABLE DESIGNATING WHETHER THE JACOBIAN MATRIX IS
    7062             : C            TO BE RECOMPUTED FOR THE COMPUTATION OF THE COVARIANCE 
    7063             : C            MATRIX (REDOJ=TRUE) OR NOT (REDOJ=FALSE).
    7064             : C   RVAR:    THE RESIDUAL VARIANCE.
    7065             : C   SDBETA:  THE STANDARD ERRORS OF THE ESTIMATED PARAMETERS.
    7066             : C   TVAL:    THE VALUE OF THE 97.5 PERCENT POINT FUNCTION FOR THE
    7067             : C            T DISTRIBUTION.
    7068             : C   WSS:     THE SUM-OF-SQUARES OF THE WEIGHTED EPSILONS AND DELTAS.
    7069             : C   WSSDEL:  THE SUM-OF-SQUARES OF THE WEIGHTED DELTAS.
    7070             : C   WSSEPS:  THE SUM-OF-SQUARES OF THE WEIGHTED EPSILONS.
    7071             : 
    7072             : 
    7073             : C***FIRST EXECUTABLE STATEMENT  DODPC3
    7074             : 
    7075             : 
    7076           0 :       D1 = INFO/10000
    7077           0 :       D2 = MOD(INFO,10000)/1000
    7078           0 :       D3 = MOD(INFO,1000)/100
    7079           0 :       D4 = MOD(INFO,100)/10
    7080           0 :       D5 = MOD(INFO,10)
    7081             : 
    7082             : C  PRINT STOPPING CONDITIONS
    7083             : 
    7084           0 :       WRITE (LUNRPT,1000)
    7085           0 :       IF (INFO.LE.9) THEN
    7086           0 :          IF (INFO.EQ.1) THEN
    7087           0 :             WRITE (LUNRPT,1011) INFO
    7088           0 :          ELSE IF (INFO.EQ.2) THEN
    7089           0 :             WRITE (LUNRPT,1012) INFO
    7090           0 :          ELSE IF (INFO.EQ.3) THEN
    7091           0 :             WRITE (LUNRPT,1013) INFO
    7092           0 :          ELSE IF (INFO.EQ.4) THEN
    7093           0 :             WRITE (LUNRPT,1014) INFO
    7094             :          ELSE IF (INFO.LE.9) THEN
    7095           0 :             WRITE (LUNRPT,1015) INFO
    7096             :          END IF
    7097           0 :       ELSE IF (INFO.LE.9999) THEN
    7098             : 
    7099             : C  PRINT WARNING DIAGNOSTICS
    7100             : 
    7101           0 :          WRITE (LUNRPT,1020) INFO
    7102           0 :          IF (D2.EQ.1) WRITE (LUNRPT,1021)
    7103           0 :          IF (D3.EQ.1) WRITE (LUNRPT,1022)
    7104           0 :          IF (D4.EQ.1) WRITE (LUNRPT,1023)
    7105           0 :          IF (D4.EQ.2) WRITE (LUNRPT,1024)
    7106           0 :          IF (D5.EQ.1) THEN
    7107           0 :             WRITE (LUNRPT,1031)
    7108           0 :          ELSE IF (D5.EQ.2) THEN
    7109           0 :             WRITE (LUNRPT,1032)
    7110           0 :          ELSE IF (D5.EQ.3) THEN
    7111           0 :             WRITE (LUNRPT,1033)
    7112           0 :          ELSE IF (D5.EQ.4) THEN
    7113           0 :             WRITE (LUNRPT,1034)
    7114             :          ELSE IF (D5.LE.9) THEN
    7115           0 :             WRITE (LUNRPT,1035) D5
    7116             :          END IF
    7117             :       ELSE
    7118             : 
    7119             : C  PRINT ERROR MESSAGES
    7120             : 
    7121           0 :          WRITE (LUNRPT,1040) INFO
    7122           0 :          IF (D1.EQ.5) THEN
    7123           0 :             WRITE (LUNRPT,1042)
    7124           0 :             IF (D2.NE.0) WRITE (LUNRPT,1043) D2
    7125           0 :             IF (D3.EQ.3) THEN
    7126           0 :                WRITE (LUNRPT,1044) D3
    7127           0 :             ELSE IF (D3.NE.0) THEN
    7128           0 :                WRITE (LUNRPT,1045) D3
    7129             :             END IF
    7130           0 :          ELSE IF (D1.EQ.6) THEN
    7131           0 :             WRITE (LUNRPT,1050)
    7132             :          ELSE
    7133           0 :             WRITE (LUNRPT,1060) D1
    7134             :          END IF
    7135             :       END IF
    7136             : 
    7137             : C  PRINT MISC. STOPPING INFO
    7138             : 
    7139           0 :       WRITE (LUNRPT,1300) NITER
    7140           0 :       WRITE (LUNRPT,1310) NFEV
    7141           0 :       IF (ANAJAC) WRITE (LUNRPT,1320) NJEV
    7142           0 :       WRITE (LUNRPT,1330) IRANK
    7143           0 :       WRITE (LUNRPT,1340) RCOND
    7144           0 :       WRITE (LUNRPT,1350) ISTOP
    7145             : 
    7146             : C  PRINT FINAL SUM OF SQUARES
    7147             : 
    7148           0 :       IF (IMPLCT) THEN
    7149           0 :          WRITE (LUNRPT,2000) WSSDEL
    7150           0 :          IF (ISODR) THEN
    7151           0 :             WRITE (LUNRPT,2010) WSS,WSSEPS,PNLTY
    7152             :          END IF
    7153             :       ELSE
    7154           0 :          WRITE (LUNRPT,2100) WSS
    7155           0 :          IF (ISODR) THEN
    7156           0 :             WRITE (LUNRPT,2110) WSSDEL,WSSEPS
    7157             :          END IF
    7158             :       END IF
    7159           0 :       IF (DIDVCV) THEN
    7160           0 :          WRITE (LUNRPT,2200) SQRT(RVAR),IDF
    7161             :       END IF
    7162             : 
    7163           0 :       NPLM1 = 3
    7164             : 
    7165             : C  PRINT ESTIMATED BETA'S, AND,
    7166             : C  IF, FULL RANK, THEIR STANDARD ERRORS
    7167             : 
    7168           0 :       WRITE (LUNRPT,3000)
    7169           0 :       IF (DIDVCV) THEN
    7170           0 :          WRITE (LUNRPT,7300)
    7171           0 :          TVAL = DPPT(0.975D0,IDF)
    7172           0 :          DO 10 J=1,NP
    7173           0 :             IF (IFIXB2(J).GE.1) THEN
    7174           0 :                WRITE (LUNRPT,8400) J,BETA(J),SDBETA(J),
    7175           0 :      +                             BETA(J)-TVAL*SDBETA(J),
    7176           0 :      +                             BETA(J)+TVAL*SDBETA(J) 
    7177           0 :             ELSE IF (IFIXB2(J).EQ.0) THEN
    7178           0 :                WRITE (LUNRPT,8600) J,BETA(J)
    7179             :             ELSE
    7180           0 :                WRITE (LUNRPT,8700) J,BETA(J)
    7181             :             END IF
    7182           0 :    10    CONTINUE
    7183           0 :          IF (.NOT.REDOJ) WRITE (LUNRPT,7310)
    7184             :       ELSE
    7185           0 :          IF (DOVCV) THEN
    7186           0 :             IF (D1.LE.5) THEN
    7187           0 :                WRITE (LUNRPT,7410)
    7188             :             ELSE
    7189           0 :                WRITE (LUNRPT,7420)
    7190             :             END IF
    7191             :          END IF
    7192             : 
    7193           0 :          IF ((IRANK.EQ.0 .AND. NPP.EQ.NP) .OR.  NITER.EQ.0) THEN
    7194           0 :             IF (NP.EQ.1) THEN
    7195           0 :                WRITE (LUNRPT,7100)
    7196             :             ELSE
    7197           0 :                WRITE (LUNRPT,7200)
    7198             :             END IF
    7199           0 :             DO 20 J=1,NP,NPLM1+1
    7200           0 :                K = MIN(J+NPLM1,NP)
    7201           0 :                IF (K.EQ.J) THEN
    7202           0 :                   WRITE (LUNRPT,8100) J,BETA(J)
    7203             :                ELSE
    7204           0 :                   WRITE (LUNRPT,8200) J,K,(BETA(L),L=J,K)
    7205             :                END IF
    7206           0 :    20       CONTINUE
    7207           0 :             IF (NITER.GE.1) THEN
    7208           0 :                WRITE (LUNRPT,8800)
    7209             :             ELSE
    7210           0 :                WRITE (LUNRPT,8900)
    7211             :             END IF
    7212             :          ELSE
    7213           0 :             WRITE (LUNRPT,7500)
    7214           0 :             DO 30 J=1,NP
    7215           0 :                IF (IFIXB2(J).GE.1) THEN
    7216           0 :                   WRITE (LUNRPT,8500) J,BETA(J)
    7217           0 :                ELSE IF (IFIXB2(J).EQ.0) THEN
    7218           0 :                   WRITE (LUNRPT,8600) J,BETA(J)
    7219             :                ELSE
    7220           0 :                   WRITE (LUNRPT,8700) J,BETA(J)
    7221             :                END IF
    7222           0 :    30       CONTINUE
    7223             :          END IF
    7224             :       END IF
    7225             : 
    7226           0 :       IF (IPR.EQ.1) RETURN
    7227             : 
    7228             : 
    7229             : C  PRINT EPSILON'S AND DELTA'S TOGETHER IN A COLUMN IF THE NUMBER OF
    7230             : C  COLUMNS OF DATA IN EPSILON AND DELTA IS LESS THAN OR EQUAL TO THREE.
    7231             : 
    7232           0 :       IF (IMPLCT .AND. (M.LE.4)) THEN
    7233           0 :          WRITE (LUNRPT,4100)
    7234           0 :          WRITE (FMT1,9110) M
    7235           0 :          WRITE (LUNRPT,FMT1) (J,J=1,M)
    7236           0 :          DO 40 I=1,N
    7237           0 :             WRITE (LUNRPT,4130) I,(DELTA(I,J),J=1,M)
    7238           0 :    40    CONTINUE
    7239             : 
    7240           0 :       ELSE IF (ISODR .AND. (NQ+M.LE.4)) THEN
    7241           0 :          WRITE (LUNRPT,4110)
    7242           0 :          WRITE (FMT1,9120) NQ,M
    7243           0 :          WRITE (LUNRPT,FMT1) (L,L=1,NQ),(J,J=1,M)
    7244           0 :          DO 50 I=1,N
    7245           0 :             WRITE (LUNRPT,4130) I,(F(I,L),L=1,NQ),(DELTA(I,J),J=1,M)
    7246           0 :    50    CONTINUE
    7247             : 
    7248           0 :       ELSE IF (.NOT.ISODR .AND. ((NQ.GE.2) .AND. (NQ.LE.4))) THEN
    7249           0 :          WRITE (LUNRPT,4120)
    7250           0 :          WRITE (FMT1,9130) NQ
    7251           0 :          WRITE (LUNRPT,FMT1) (L,L=1,NQ)
    7252           0 :          DO 60 I=1,N
    7253           0 :             WRITE (LUNRPT,4130) I,(F(I,L),L=1,NQ)
    7254           0 :    60    CONTINUE
    7255             :       ELSE
    7256             : 
    7257             : C  PRINT EPSILON'S AND DELTA'S SEPARATELY
    7258             : 
    7259           0 :          IF (.NOT.IMPLCT) THEN
    7260             : 
    7261             : C  PRINT EPSILON'S
    7262             : 
    7263           0 :             DO 80 J=1,NQ
    7264           0 :                WRITE (LUNRPT,4200) J
    7265           0 :                IF (N.EQ.1) THEN
    7266           0 :                   WRITE (LUNRPT,7100)
    7267             :                ELSE
    7268           0 :                   WRITE (LUNRPT,7200)
    7269             :                END IF
    7270           0 :                DO 70 I=1,N,NPLM1+1
    7271           0 :                   K = MIN(I+NPLM1,N)
    7272           0 :                   IF (I.EQ.K) THEN
    7273           0 :                      WRITE (LUNRPT,8100) I,F(I,J)
    7274             :                   ELSE
    7275           0 :                      WRITE (LUNRPT,8200) I,K,(F(L,J),L=I,K)
    7276             :                   END IF
    7277           0 :    70          CONTINUE
    7278           0 :    80       CONTINUE
    7279             :          END IF
    7280             : 
    7281             : C  PRINT DELTA'S
    7282             : 
    7283           0 :          IF (ISODR) THEN
    7284           0 :             DO 100 J=1,M
    7285           0 :                WRITE (LUNRPT,4300) J
    7286           0 :                IF (N.EQ.1) THEN
    7287           0 :                   WRITE (LUNRPT,7100)
    7288             :                ELSE
    7289           0 :                   WRITE (LUNRPT,7200)
    7290             :                END IF
    7291           0 :                DO 90 I=1,N,NPLM1+1
    7292           0 :                   K = MIN(I+NPLM1,N)
    7293           0 :                   IF (I.EQ.K) THEN
    7294           0 :                      WRITE (LUNRPT,8100) I,DELTA(I,J)
    7295             :                   ELSE
    7296           0 :                      WRITE (LUNRPT,8200) I,K,(DELTA(L,J),L=I,K)
    7297             :                   END IF
    7298           0 :    90          CONTINUE
    7299           0 :   100       CONTINUE
    7300             :          END IF
    7301             :       END IF
    7302             : 
    7303             :       RETURN

    8048             : *DODPE2
    8049           0 :       SUBROUTINE DODPE2
    8050             :      +   (UNIT,
    8051             :      +   N,M,NP,NQ,

    8060             : C***PURPOSE  GENERATE THE DERIVATIVE CHECKING REPORT

    8062             : 
    8063             : C...SCALAR ARGUMENTS

    8094             : C   J:       AN INDEX VARIABLE.
    8095             : C   K:       AN INDEX VARIABLE.

    8106             : C   NROW:    THE ROW NUMBER OF THE EXPLANATORY VARIABLE ARRAY AT

    8112             : C   XPLUSD:  THE VALUES OF X + DELTA.

    8115             : C***FIRST EXECUTABLE STATEMENT  DODPE2
    8116             : 
    8117             :

    8121           0 :          FTNOTE(I) = .FALSE.

    8169             :             ELSE IF (K.GE.1) THEN

    8171             :             END IF
    8172           0 :    50    CONTINUE

    8179           0 :                   FLAG = ' '

    8187           0 :                   WRITE (UNIT,4300) NROW,I, 
    8188           0 :      +                              FJACD(NROW,I,L),DIFF(L,NP+I),FLAG,K
    8189             :                END IF

    8191             :          END IF
    8192           0 :    70 CONTINUE
    8193             : 
    8194             : C     PRINT FOOTNOTES
    8195             :

    8197             :

    8199           0 :          IF (FTNOTE(1)) WRITE (UNIT,5100)
    8200           0 :          IF (FTNOTE(2)) WRITE (UNIT,5200)

    9440             : C   P:       THE PROBABILITY AT WHICH THE PERCENT POINT IS TO BE 
    9441             : C            EVALUATED.  P MUST BE BETWEEN 0.0D0 AND 1.0D0, EXCLUSIVE. 
    9442             : C   P0:      A PARAMETER USED IN THE APPROXIMATION.
    9443             : C   P1:      A PARAMETER USED IN THE APPROXIMATION.
    9444             : C   P2:      A PARAMETER USED IN THE APPROXIMATION.
    9445             : C   P3:      A PARAMETER USED IN THE APPROXIMATION.
    9446             : C   P4:      A PARAMETER USED IN THE APPROXIMATION.
    9447             : C   Q0:      A PARAMETER USED IN THE APPROXIMATION.
    9448             : C   Q1:      A PARAMETER USED IN THE APPROXIMATION.
    9449             : C   Q2:      A PARAMETER USED IN THE APPROXIMATION.
    9450             : C   Q3:      A PARAMETER USED IN THE APPROXIMATION.
    9451             : C   Q4:      A PARAMETER USED IN THE APPROXIMATION.
    9452             : C   R:       THE PROBABILITY AT WHICH THE PERCENT POINT IS EVALUATED.
    9453             : C   T:       A VALUE USED IN THE APPROXIMATION.
    9454             : C   TWO:     THE VALUE 2.0D0.
    9455             : C   ZERO:    THE VALUE 0.0D0.
    9456             : 
    9457             : 
    9458             : C***FIRST EXECUTABLE STATEMENT  DPPT
    9459             : 
    9460             : 
    9461           0 :       IF (P.EQ.HALF) THEN
    9462           0 :          DPPNML = ZERO
    9463             : 
    9464             :       ELSE
    9465           0 :          R = P
    9466           0 :          IF (P.GT.HALF) R = ONE - R 
    9467           0 :          T = SQRT(-TWO*LOG(R)) 
    9468           0 :          ANUM = ((((T*P4+P3)*T+P2)*T+P1)*T+P0)
    9469           0 :          ADEN = ((((T*Q4+Q3)*T+Q2)*T+Q1)*T+Q0)
    9470           0 :          DPPNML = T + (ANUM/ADEN)
    9471             : 
    9472           0 :          IF (P.LT.HALF) DPPNML = -DPPNML
    9473             :       END IF
    9474             : 
    9475             :       RETURN
    9476             : 
    9477             :       END

    9487             : C             STATISTICAL ENGINEERING DIVISION

    9489             : C             WASHINGTON, D. C. 20234

    9491             : C             (UPDATED         --NOVEMBER  1975.)
    9492             : C***PURPOSE  COMPUTE THE PERCENT POINT FUNCTION VALUE FOR THE

    9501             : C                IS AUGMENTED BY 3 ITERATIONS OF NEWTON'S METHOD TO
    9502             : C                IMPROVE THE ACCURACY, ESPECIALLY FOR P NEAR 0 OR 1.

    9607             :

    9609           0 :       PI = 3.141592653589793238462643383279D0
    9610           0 :       DF = IDF
    9611           0 :       MAXIT = 5
    9612             : 
    9613           0 :       IF (IDF.LE.0) THEN
    9614             : 
    9615             : C  TREAT THE IDF < 1 CASE
    9616           0 :          DPPT = ZERO
    9617             : 
    9618           0 :       ELSE IF (IDF.EQ.1) THEN
    9619             : 
    9620             : C  TREAT THE IDF = 1 (CAUCHY) CASE
    9621           0 :          ARG = PI*P
    9622           0 :          DPPT = -COS(ARG)/SIN(ARG)
    9623             : 
    9624           0 :       ELSE IF (IDF.EQ.2) THEN
    9625             : 
    9626             : C  TREAT THE IDF = 2 CASE
    9627           0 :          TERM1 = SQRT(TWO)/TWO
    9628           0 :          TERM2 = TWO*P - ONE
    9629           0 :          TERM3 = SQRT(P*(ONE-P)) 
    9630           0 :          DPPT = TERM1*TERM2/TERM3
    9631             : 
    9632             :       ELSE IF (IDF.GE.3) THEN
    9633             : 
    9634             : C  TREAT THE IDF GREATER THAN OR EQUAL TO 3 CASE
    9635           0 :          PPFN = DPPNML(P)
    9636           0 :          D1 = PPFN
    9637           0 :          D3 = PPFN**3
    9638           0 :          D5 = PPFN**5
    9639           0 :          D7 = PPFN**7
    9640           0 :          D9 = PPFN**9
    9641           0 :          TERM1 = D1
    9642           0 :          TERM2 = (ONE/B21)*(D3+D1)/DF
    9643           0 :          TERM3 = (ONE/B31)*(B32*D5+B33*D3+B34*D1)/(DF**2)
    9644           0 :          TERM4 = (ONE/B41)*(B42*D7+B43*D5+B44*D3+B45*D1)/(DF**3) 
    9645           0 :          TERM5 = (ONE/B51)*(B52*D9+B53*D7+B54*D5+B55*D3+B56*D1)/(DF**4)
    9646           0 :          DPPT = TERM1 + TERM2 + TERM3 + TERM4 + TERM5
    9647             : 
    9648           0 :          IF (IDF.EQ.3) THEN
    9649             : 
    9650             : C  AUGMENT THE RESULTS FOR THE IDF = 3 CASE
    9651           0 :             CON = PI*(P-HALF)
    9652           0 :             ARG = DPPT/SQRT(DF)
    9653           0 :             Z = ATAN(ARG)
    9654           0 :             DO 70 IPASS=1,MAXIT
    9655           0 :                S = SIN(Z)
    9656           0 :                C = COS(Z)
    9657           0 :                Z = Z - (Z+S*C-CON)/(TWO*C**2)
    9658           0 :    70       CONTINUE
    9659           0 :             DPPT = SQRT(DF)*S/C
    9660             : 
    9661           0 :          ELSE IF (IDF.EQ.4) THEN
    9662             : 
    9663             : C  AUGMENT THE RESULTS FOR THE IDF = 4 CASE
    9664           0 :             CON = TWO*(P-HALF)
    9665           0 :             ARG = DPPT/SQRT(DF)
    9666           0 :             Z = ATAN(ARG)
    9667           0 :             DO 90 IPASS=1,MAXIT
    9668           0 :                S = SIN(Z)
    9669           0 :                C = COS(Z)
    9670           0 :                Z = Z - ((ONE+HALF*C**2)*S-CON)/((ONE+HALF)*C**3)
    9671           0 :    90       CONTINUE
    9672           0 :             DPPT = SQRT(DF)*S/C
    9673             : 
    9674           0 :          ELSE IF (IDF.EQ.5) THEN
    9675             : 
    9676             : C  AUGMENT THE RESULTS FOR THE IDF = 5 CASE
    9677             : 
    9678           0 :             CON = PI*(P-HALF)
    9679           0 :             ARG = DPPT/SQRT(DF)
    9680           0 :             Z = ATAN(ARG)
    9681           0 :             DO 110 IPASS=1,MAXIT
    9682           0 :                S = SIN(Z)
    9683           0 :                C = COS(Z)
    9684             :                Z = Z - (Z+(C+(TWO/THREE)*C**3)*S-CON)/
    9685           0 :      +                 ((EIGHT/THREE)*C**4) 
    9686           0 :   110       CONTINUE
    9687           0 :             DPPT = SQRT(DF)*S/C
    9688             : 
    9689           0 :          ELSE IF (IDF.EQ.6) THEN
    9690             : 
    9691             : C  AUGMENT THE RESULTS FOR THE IDF = 6 CASE
    9692           0 :             CON = TWO*(P-HALF) 
    9693           0 :             ARG = DPPT/SQRT(DF)
    9694           0 :             Z = ATAN(ARG)
    9695           0 :             DO 130 IPASS=1,MAXIT
    9696           0 :                S = SIN(Z)
    9697           0 :                C = COS(Z)
    9698             :                Z = Z - ((ONE+HALF*C**2 + (THREE/EIGHT)*C**4)*S-CON)/
    9699           0 :      +                 ((FIFTN/EIGHT)*C**5)
    9700           0 :   130       CONTINUE
    9701           0 :             DPPT = SQRT(DF)*S/C
    9702             :          END IF
    9703             :       END IF
    9704             : 
    9705             :       RETURN
    9706             :
